<br>
I am curious what the the shaman's AC and HPs were? If the shaman was taking aggro from 15-20 shrooms/underbulks/dregs etc at a time, he must have been taking some damage - was he just constantly casting torpor on himself through both the pulls and the fight? Finally, how long did the fights last normally?<br>
<br>
Sorry for so many questions, but I play both a mage and a shaman so hearing of these kind of tactics is very exciting!<br>
<br>
Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulianadmagi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lianad Magi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(6/22/02 9:23:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  .</span><hr size=1> Grizl,<br>
<br>
  I honestly don't know what the shaman's hp/ac were but I can tell you things I noticed.  Typically when he was rounding up the shrooms he barely took any damage, I barely saw his hp bar move at all.  On some occasions though after he had about 15 rounded up you would see his hp bar start to drop a tad.. My assumption from seeing the shrooms up close is that once slowed they hardly ever hit, and spend 90% of the time casting which I resisted every single time so I assume the shaman resisted as well.  When we were Aeing the shrooms I very rarely ever got hit, but I did get a ton of resist messages from their spells..<br>
<br>
   When the shaman pulled the dregs, I probalby didn't clarify enough.  He never pulled a group of 10 - 15 dregs or else he probably would have been dead.  He would usually pull 1-3 dregs first and bring them back to us to sick pets on, then would go round up about 10 15 shrooms and bring them back.  This way by time we were done AEing shrooms, the dregs would be dead same time. (dregs have much more hp then shrooms).<br>
<br>
    So technically after thinking about this, this method probably own't work in a lot of cases where mobs have tons of hp and hit very hard.  Reason being is shaman would be dead by time he brought them back.  But in cases like FG with the shrooms who seem to just cast/miss once slowed, its a perfect spot..<br>
<br>
Lianad Staffborn<br>
