<br>
The shammy I play with has c5 otherwise mana will be a bit tight. Only thing to be careful of is timing. If you take to long pulling them and the slows start to wear off it can be dangerous.<br>
<br>
Pet hold also make a difference as that means the mage can go out and help get aggro on some of the pulled mushies as it can be difficult for the shammy to keep more than 10+ mushies aggro while pulling.<br>
<br>
Also had a warrior friend of mine join us once with earthshaker. With the rampage ability and avatar he managed to do about 20k damage. Also can help with pulling. <br>
<br>
My record so far is about 20 mushies at once. The exp is the best you will ever get. I can get almost a full  AA every 2 hrs if not many other people in zone.<br>
<br>
Hardest part these days is finding enough mushies up to pull. With the 3 person group we can keep all the spawns before the tunnel clear fairly easily. Luckily I am an Aussie so FG is less packed when I play.<br>
<br>
